They&#x27;re not required, they just default to having a name. You can tell the compiler you don&#x27;t want a name, and it works:<p><pre><code>    func f(a: Int)(_ b: Int)(_ c: Int) -> Int { return a + b + c }
    let v = f(2)(5)(5)
</code></pre>
The rules for what gets an externally visible name automatically are pretty weird, to be sure. But it&#x27;s easy to have it do what you want if you don&#x27;t want the default.
